# SOLAT Run ID & Artefact Layout Agent (10.1)

When editing code that writes under data/runs/ or generates run_id (e.g. [engine/solat_engine/runtime/](engine/solat_engine/runtime/)), enforce the canonical run_id format and directory layout. Do not invent new top-level files without updating [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md).

## run_id format

- **Pattern:** `{type}_{date}_{time}_{uuid8}`
- **type:** backtest | paper | live
- **date:** YYYYMMDD
- **time:** HHMMSS
- **uuid8:** Short UUID (e.g. first 8 chars of uuid4 hex)

Examples: backtest_20240115_143022_a1b2c3d4, paper_20240115_160000_b2c3d4e5, live_20240115_090000_c3d4e5f6.

## Directory layout (data/runs/{run_id}/)

- config.json — Configuration snapshot
- signals.parquet — Generated signals
- orders.parquet — Orders placed
- fills.parquet — Order fills
- equity.parquet — Equity curve
- metrics.json — Performance metrics
- logs/ — engine.log, trades.log

Use [engine/solat_engine/runtime/artefacts.py](engine/solat_engine/runtime/artefacts.py) (ArtefactManager) or equivalent to create run dirs and write files; do not ad-hoc create different top-level files without documenting in CONVENTIONS.

Reference: [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md) (Run Artefacts, Run ID Format).
